  <name>Komi Store</name>
  <summary>App store for GitHub, Codeberg, and Forgejo releases</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      Komi Store lets you browse, download, and keep track of applications
      distributed through GitHub, Codeberg, and other Forgejo-based release pages.
      It brings the convenience of an app store to the open-source ecosystem.
    </p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Discover trending, hot, and popular repositories with installable releases</li>
      <li>Search and filter repositories by language, topic, and more</li>
      <li>View release notes, changelogs, and READMEs with built-in translation</li>
      <li>Verify installs with TOFU signing-key checks and provenance attestation</li>
      <li>Save favourites and starred repositories for quick access</li>
      <li>Sign in with GitHub for higher API rate limits and a personalized feed</li>
      <li>Material 3 theming with light/dark mode and 13 language translations</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Note: inside the Flatpak sandbox, Komi Store downloads release assets to your
      Downloads folder for you to install manually. It does not install or update
      system packages on your behalf.
    </p>
  </description>

